&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;About this role:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MATTE is looking for a Senior Experiential Producer to join its fast-growing Experiential department. The Senior Producer will be responsible for leading high-end experiential production for a variety of clients. This role requires strong creative production capabilities with a working understanding of technical production (AV, lighting, scenic, staging, fabrication) to confidently manage technical partners and ensure feasibility throughout the project lifecycle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior Producer reports to the Director of Experiential and works closely with project team leads across the organization. This role also contributes to the management of the production team, which includes both full-time and contracted staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;The Senior Producer is responsible for leading experiential production for projects from kickoff through delivery and wrap, including:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing creative and technical experiential production that includes but is not limited to: building production plans and schedules, shepherding creative direction, overseeing junior production team members, and sourcing/managing all production vendors and partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating with technical vendors, fabrication partners, and AV teams to ensure technical feasibility across all experiential components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reviewing and providing directional feedback on technical documents such as renderings, gear lists, and shop drawings (with support from technical partners as needed).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Overseeing on-site installation, testing, and load-in with a general understanding of technical workflows and the ability to troubleshoot with vendors on the ground.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing and executing project scopes, timelines, budgets, and staffing plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring compliance with all relevant regulations, permits, and licenses for events and activations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing and representing MATTE’s experiential production expertise internally and externally, ensuring the highest quality creative and technical execution while keeping feasibility and timelines grounded in reality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitoring out-of-scope requests and initiating additional estimates and approvals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sourcing vendors and contractors as needed for all programs, including fabrication, scenic, AV, lighting, and specialty tech partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building, managing, and wrapping project budgets ranging in scale and complexity, maximizing profitability in partnership with the Director of Experiential.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervising staff throughout the project lifecycle, reviewing and troubleshooting potential issues that may impact deadlines or deliverables.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating with cross-functional teams including Client Services, Creative, Strategy, and Operations to ensure seamless project integration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working within specific brand guidelines and bringing projects from concept to production while maintaining consistency, high standards, and technical accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
